Pronotum approximately 1.25 times as wide as head and 1.30 times as wide as long (
Fig. 92
); maximal width approximately in the middle; puncturation very dense, much coarser than that of head, and somewhat asperate; microsculpture very shallow; surface with subdued shine.

Elytra approximately as wide as pronotum and at suture 0.70 times as long as pronotum (
Fig. 92
); puncturation coarser than that of pronotum, very dense, and rasp-like; microsculpture indistinct; surface with some shine. Hind wings reduced, not projecting from under elytral hind margins when unfolded (
Fig. 85
). Legs relatively short; metatarsomere I longer than the combined length of the two following metatarsomeres, but shorter than the combined length of metatarsomeres II-IV.

Abdomen approximately as wide as elytra, widest at segments VI/VII, apically weakly tapering (
Fig. 92
); puncturation distinct and very dense on tergite III, decreasing in density from tergites IV to VIII; microsculpture absent, interstices with distinct shine; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe.
